The paper focuses on context-aware access control for mobile devices, which involves security and privacy concerns (cs.CR). The authors also emphasize the importance of usability and user-centered design, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of context data for personalized access control also relates to the field of social computing (cs.SI). The implementation of the framework and its integration with a fine-grained access control architecture suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of contextual privacy, which is a topic in the field of cyber security (cs.CY).
